---
description: Always apply — factual discipline
alwaysApply: true
---

- Never invent metrics, statistics, or rankings.
- If you cannot verify a claim from the provided files or context, say so explicitly.
- When analysing a website, only describe what is observable in the provided 
  source files or screenshots. Do not assume what is not shown.
- If MCP data is unavailable, note it and proceed with what is available.
